                                                                                               Ultimately, authorization decisions (i.e., risk acceptance decisions) are made based on the
                                                                                               degree to which the desired security and privacy capabilities have been effectively achieved and
                                                                                               are meeting the security and privacy requirements defined by an organization. Risk-based
                                                                                               decisions are directly related to organizational risk tolerance that is defined as part of an
                                                                                               organizationâ€™s risk management strategy.


                                                                                                                                      CAPABILITY-BASED ASSESSMENTS

                                                                                               The grouping of controls into security and privacy capabilities necessitates root cause analyses to
                                                                                               determine if the failure of a particular security or privacy capability can be traced to the failure of one or
                                                                                               more security or privacy controls based on the established relationships among controls. The structure of
                                                                                               the assessment procedures in this publication with the token-level decomposition and labelling of
                                                                                               assessment objectives linked to the specific content of security and privacy controls supports such root
                                                                                               cause analysis. Thus, assessments of security and privacy controls (defined as part of capabilities) can be
                                                                                               tailored based on the guidance in Section 3.2.3 and [SP 800-137] to define the resource expenditures
                                                                                               (e.g., frequency and level of effort) associated with such assessments. This additional precision in
                                                                                               assessments is essential to supporting the continuous monitoring strategies developed by organizations
                                                                                               and the ongoing authorization decisions of senior leaders.




